WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:23.991 --> 00:24.940
Hello?

00:24.942 --> 00:27.659
I'm gonna get you.

00:27.661 --> 00:29.628
I'm gonna get you.

00:29.630 --> 00:32.363
Stop it. I mean it.
This isn't funny anymore.

00:32.366 --> 00:34.716
Stop calling here.

00:39.555 --> 00:40.973
Who was it?

00:40.975 --> 00:42.507
That damn kid again.

00:42.509 --> 00:47.012
I can't believe the police
won't do anything about it.

00:47.014 --> 00:49.431
Where have you been?

00:49.433 --> 00:53.018
I couldn't sleep.
I went downstairs to watch TV

00:53.020 --> 00:55.153
and I conked out
on the couch.

00:56.105 --> 00:59.358
Isn't that guy at your office
a retired cop--

00:59.360 --> 01:00.409
Jake?

01:00.411 --> 01:01.526
Yeah.

01:01.528 --> 01:05.129
Can you talk to him?

01:05.132 --> 01:07.032
What's he gonna do?

01:07.034 --> 01:08.250
I don't know.

01:08.252 --> 01:10.502
I just want somebody
to do something.

01:10.504 --> 01:14.222
That kid'll get bored
soon enough.

01:22.632 --> 01:26.101
Ok, I'll talk to Jake.

01:33.776 --> 01:36.928
Andy, breakfast is ready!

01:36.930 --> 01:37.929
Hi.
Mmm.

01:37.931 --> 01:39.264
Mwah!

01:39.266 --> 01:40.449
Can you please
take Kozmo out?

01:40.451 --> 01:42.451
- Hey!
- Kozmo!

01:42.453 --> 01:44.152
Kozmo, come on.

01:44.154 --> 01:45.320
Andy!
Let's go, buddy.

01:45.322 --> 01:47.406
You're gonna be late!

01:47.408 --> 01:49.241
Andy!

01:49.243 --> 01:51.609
Andrew Taffert,

01:51.611 --> 01:55.113
you cannot
miss the bus again.

02:01.620 --> 02:05.424
You're supposed to be up.
I'm gonna pour cold water on you.

02:12.148 --> 02:13.598
Andy?

02:24.444 --> 02:27.579
Andy's not in his room.
Have you seen him?

02:29.332 --> 02:30.982
Oh, my God!

02:30.984 --> 02:32.484
What is that?

02:33.586 --> 02:34.836
Andy?!

02:34.838 --> 02:36.154
Andy!

02:36.156 --> 02:37.155
Where is he?

02:37.157 --> 02:38.156
I don't know.

02:38.158 --> 02:39.324
I'm calling the police.

02:39.326 --> 02:40.325
Andy!

02:40.327 --> 02:42.094
Andy?

02:51.472 --> 02:53.472
Did you see
what I did?

02:53.474 --> 02:55.941
Did you see it?

02:55.943 --> 02:57.442
We just got a call
from St. Louis.

02:57.444 --> 02:59.995
A missing child, a 10-year-old,
Andrew Taffert.

02:59.997 --> 03:01.446
Parents Lida
and Malcolm.

03:01.448 --> 03:04.065
Father found blood on the front
door this morning.

03:04.067 --> 03:06.118
I take it no test results
on the blood yet.

03:06.120 --> 03:07.702
No. That
would be correct.

03:07.704 --> 03:09.237
No signs of forced entry
or a struggle

03:09.239 --> 03:11.189
according to the initial
police report.

03:11.191 --> 03:12.524
Mom and dad put him
to bed at 10:00,

03:12.526 --> 03:13.858
woke up this morning,
he was gone.

03:13.860 --> 03:16.661
Any visitors or workers
to the house recently?

03:16.663 --> 03:18.914
No. But the parents say
in the last two weeks

03:18.916 --> 03:20.499
they've received
5 phone calls

03:20.501 --> 03:22.584
from what sounds like
a little boy prank calling them.

03:22.586 --> 03:24.421
They complained to authorities,
but police determined that

03:24.446 --> 03:25.588
no laws had been broken.

03:25.589 --> 03:27.088
Mm-hmm. The little boy
says, "I'm gonna get you."

03:27.090 --> 03:29.674
According the police reports,
there's a lot of crazy people

03:29.676 --> 03:31.162
talking in the background.

03:31.187 --> 03:33.012
It sounds like it's coming
from an asylum or a prison.

03:33.013 --> 03:34.563
I'd say the calls
might be coincidental

03:34.565 --> 03:36.359
except the boy called again
right after the parents

03:36.384 --> 03:38.018
found Andy missing,
and he had a different

03:38.019 --> 03:39.914
message this time.
"Did you see what I did?"

03:40.687 --> 03:42.020
So he's taunting them.

03:42.022 --> 03:43.688
Maybe this is about revenge.

03:43.690 --> 03:45.941
"I'm gonna get you"
is typically a threat,

03:45.943 --> 03:47.328
but in the case of children,

03:47.329 --> 03:49.829
it can also be a phrase
used during play.

03:49.830 --> 03:52.614
This sounds similar
to a cold case from 15 years ago,

03:52.616 --> 03:54.399
Frankie Clayvin
of Memphis.

03:54.401 --> 03:56.234
I remember that
Gideon handled it.

03:56.236 --> 03:58.286
It obviously
it predates all of you.

03:58.288 --> 03:59.955
Frankie Clayvin
was 9 years old at the time.

03:59.957 --> 04:01.423
He never made it home
from school one day.

04:01.425 --> 04:03.908
He was found dead
in the woods 36 hours later

04:03.910 --> 04:05.460
5 miles
from his house.

04:05.462 --> 04:06.911
And Frankie's parents
also received

04:06.913 --> 04:09.047
prank phone calls
from a young boy.

04:09.049 --> 04:12.234
I think Frankie's father
was the prime suspect at one point.

04:12.236 --> 04:14.352
Yeah, the police actually
tapped the Clayvins' phone,

04:14.354 --> 04:15.720
but they couldn't
trace the phone calls

04:15.722 --> 04:17.255
because they kept bouncing
between different pay phones

04:17.257 --> 04:18.473
in the greater
Memphis area.

04:18.475 --> 04:19.940
Phone calls before
an abduction-murder--

04:19.942 --> 04:21.259
it's a rare signature.

04:21.261 --> 04:22.727
But if it is
the same unsub,

04:22.729 --> 04:24.596
a dormancy period
of 15 years is highly unusual.

04:24.598 --> 04:26.198
Maybe we're looking
at a copycat.

04:26.200 --> 04:27.319
If I'm not mistaken,

04:27.344 --> 04:29.101
Frankie Clayvin was
killed within two hours

04:29.102 --> 04:30.268
of his abduction.

04:30.270 --> 04:32.103
Which means we're
wasting time. Let's go.

04:34.907 --> 04:37.292
911. What is your emergency?

04:37.294 --> 04:38.910
My son is gone!

04:38.912 --> 04:41.613
I checked his room
this morning and he's gone!

04:41.615 --> 04:44.115
I can't--

04:44.117 --> 04:45.984
We can't find him
anywhere.

04:45.986 --> 04:47.285
He's only 10.

04:47.287 --> 04:49.487
Ok, ma'am. We're sending
a unit right away.

04:49.489 --> 04:50.622
What's your son's name?

04:50.624 --> 04:52.807
We have a missing child

04:52.809 --> 04:54.292
at 472 Oakdale Drive,

04:54.294 --> 04:56.478
last seen yesterday
at 2100 hours.

04:56.480 --> 04:58.763
Andrew Taffert, born 2003,

04:58.765 --> 05:01.967
4 feet 7 inches,
short blond hair, blue eyes,

05:01.969 --> 05:05.070
wearing an orange sweatshirt
and plaid pajama pants.

05:05.072 --> 05:06.938
We're labeling as suspicious
circumstances

05:06.940 --> 05:09.274
and a possible abduction.

05:10.082 --> 05:14.082
